President Muhammadu Buhari will today convene a council of state meeting. This is the first council of state meeting this year. The earlier
scheduled meeting in March this year was postponed because of the
Covid-19 pandemic. The council of state meeting today will be a virtual one. The Council of State consists of the following persons: President, who
is the Chairman; Vice President, who is the Deputy Chairman; all former
Presidents of the Federation and all former Heads of the Government of
the Federation.  Others are “All former Chief Justices of Nigeria; President of the
Senate; Speaker of the House of Representatives; All the Governors of
the states of the Federation; and Attorney-General of the Federation.  LEADERSHIP gathered that the coronavirus pandemic and insecurity would
top the agenda of the meeting.  Meanwhile, President Muhammadu Buhari yesterday sworn-in 12 permanent
secretaries. The president held the ceremony just before the commencement of the
weekly virtual Federal Executive Council (FEC) meeting at the State
House, Abuja. The permanent secretaries were appointed in June in a statement issued
by the Head of Service of the Federation (HoSF), Dr. Folasade
Yemi-Esan.
The newly appointed permanent secretaries and their states are:
Belgore Shuaib Mohammad Lomido, Kwara; Akinlade Oluwatoyin, Kogi; Ekpa
Anthonia Akpabio, Cross River; Alkali Bashir Nura, Kano; Ardo Babayo
Kumo, Gombe and Anyanwutaku Adaora lfeoma, Anambra. Others are: Udoh
Moniloja Omokunmi, Oyo; Hussaini Babangida, Jigawa; Mohammed Aliyu
Ganda, Sokoto; Mahmuda Mamman, Yobe; Meribole Emmanuel Chukwuemeka,
Abia and Tarfa Yerima Peter Adamawa.
The President also swore in commissioners for Federal Civil Service
Commission, Idahagbon Henry and Revenue Mobilisation Allocation and
Fiscal Commission, Usman Hassan.